        "content": "<p>The doc-string of <code>Name.isInternal</code> claims that</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">The</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">frontend</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">does</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">allow</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">user</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">declarations</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">start</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ss\">`_</span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">any</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">its</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">parts</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"n\">We</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">name</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">parts</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">starting</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ss\">`_</span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">internally</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">create</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">auxiliary</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">names</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">g</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ss\">`_private</span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>However, if I type <code>def _foo := 5</code>, Lean doesn't complain. Should it?</p>\n<p>As a result you can write names starting with <code>_private.</code>, which Lean will think is a private name, even if it wasn't labelled with <code>private</code>.</p>",
